Key Match Events: Tyler O'Neill hit a walk-off home run in the 10th inning to give the Red Sox a 5-3 victory over the Orioles.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Alex Cora stated, 'We just won a series against one of the best teams in the big leagues. Obviously, in our situation, it’s not enough. We’ve got to continue.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game went into 10 innings due to a 3-3 tie.
Nick Pivetta pitched six strong innings, allowing just four hits and one walk.
Tyler O'Neill's home run was his second walk-off winner of the season.
